# Optional per-repo Cloudflare config. The real .env.cloudflare.local is
# git-ignored and merged into the directory-local wrangler env (see
# scripts/cf-env.mjs) for the `vp run wrangler` and `vp run deploy` tasks.
#
# Auth is normally done once with `vp run wrangler login` (writes the OAuth
# token under .wrangler-local/), so you usually do NOT need API keys here.
# To use an API token instead of OAuth, uncomment:
# CLOUDFLARE_API_TOKEN=
# CLOUDFLARE_ACCOUNT_ID=
